{
  "texts": [
    "This method adapts to changing research objectives and facilitates resource integration, demonstrating the importance of dynamic KGs in realtime control and mitigating geographical constraints.In human-robot collaboration, Ding et al. [53] used KGs to enhance complex tasks like disassembly, equipping robots with improved knowledge and reasoning capabilities.",
    "Peng et al. [54] further explored challenges in KGs, such as addressing long-tail knowledge, biases, and the need for explainability and interpretability.Context representation is crucial for robotic systems.",
    "While ontologies provide structured knowledge, they lack efficient visualization and querying.",
    "Dimitropoulos et al. [55] proposed a hybrid approach, converting ontologies into KGs to combine their strengths, offering better consistency and accessibility for robotic applications.",
    "However, KGs lack logical consistency checking, a feature of ontologies.Recent advancements in KG frameworks, such as OpenKE [56] and PyTorch-BigGraph [57], have enhanced the scal-ability and efficiency of knowledge representation, enabling their application in complex robotic systems."
  ]
}